---<rule>
  <name>Forensic UI & Viewfinder Performance</name>
  <description>Enforces the Technical/Forensic design language and protects camera frame rates.</description>
  <action>
    - REQUIRE typography for all HUD, telemetry, hashes, timestamps, and ledger identifiers to use a monospaced technical font (prefer `GoogleFonts.spaceMono` through `AppTextStyles`).
    - FORBID thick borders, solid containers, or drop shadows over the camera feed. Use stark, thin lines (`strokeWidth: 1.0` or `1.5`) and high contrast.
    - REQUIRE the use of `CustomPaint` for camera frames, reticles, crosshairs, and the capture shutter to minimize the widget tree depth.
    - REQUIRE all UI overlays operating on top of the live camera feed to be wrapped in `RepaintBoundary`.
    - REQUIRE the capture control to use the mechanical iris motif via `ShutterIrisPainter` inside a `RepaintBoundary`.
    - COLOR PALETTE: Primary surfaces use Titanium Deep (`0xFF121212`) and Titanium Panel (`0xFF1C1C1C`); primary UI text uses Stark White (`0xFFFFFFFF`); active/in-progress states use Kinetic Green (`0xFF00D26A`); completed locked/verified states use Verified Neon (`0xFF39FF14`).
  </action>
</rule>
alwaysApply: true
---
